282
00:19:32,442 --> 00:19:33,474
Okay.

283
00:19:34,843 --> 00:19:37,545
We can work the ranch together,

284
00:19:37,547 --> 00:19:38,880
as a family.

285
00:19:42,917 --> 00:19:44,552
[George]: Hey, wait for me!

286
00:19:44,554 --> 00:19:47,288
[Kids laugh]

287
00:19:48,457 --> 00:19:52,626
You're mine now, you understand that?

288
00:19:52,628 --> 00:19:53,860
You mind me,

289
00:19:53,862 --> 00:19:54,928
and I care for you

290
00:19:54,930 --> 00:19:56,630
and keep you.

291
00:19:56,632 --> 00:19:57,798
Yes, ma'am.

292
00:19:57,800 --> 00:19:58,899
Ma.

293
00:19:58,901 --> 00:19:59,967
To you both.

294
00:20:01,268 --> 00:20:03,470
This morning, we were two.

295
00:20:03,472 --> 00:20:05,371
Now we're six.

296
00:20:08,375 --> 00:20:09,977
[♪]

297
00:20:09,979 --> 00:20:10,978
[Flashbulb crackles]

298
00:20:16,917 --> 00:20:17,917
I want to come, too.

299
00:20:17,919 --> 00:20:21,421
No. There's one horse and it's for me.

300
00:20:21,423 --> 00:20:23,590
We've organized a hunting party.

301
00:20:23,592 --> 00:20:24,890
Mr. Loving's to lead us.

302
00:20:24,892 --> 00:20:27,627
He's been on safari in Africa.

303
00:20:27,629 --> 00:20:29,829
When... when will you be back, then?

304
00:20:29,831 --> 00:20:31,430
Well, Mr. and Mrs. Loving
have recently been married.

305
00:20:31,432 --> 00:20:32,932
They haven't a chance to celebrate,

306
00:20:32,934 --> 00:20:35,735
so I arranged a wedding party.

307
00:20:41,041 --> 00:20:42,608
It's a fitting goodbye

308
00:20:42,610 --> 00:20:47,279
to be among these people,
in the middle of life.

309
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:03,962
It's a wedding party, for us.

310
00:21:05,497 --> 00:21:07,331
Come on, Kat.

311
00:21:09,434 --> 00:21:10,835
I saw a woman with a dead baby yesterday.

312
00:21:14,073 --> 00:21:16,307
I have the feeling of death all around me.

313
00:21:19,744 --> 00:21:22,413
You and I...

314
00:21:22,415 --> 00:21:23,914
will be together forever.

315
00:21:25,016 --> 00:21:28,085
We'll be surrounded by our children,

316
00:21:28,087 --> 00:21:29,620
and there will be generations of us

317
00:21:29,622 --> 00:21:32,356
to the end of the world.

318
00:21:54,845 --> 00:21:56,546
Mrs. Blithely.

319
00:21:56,548 --> 00:21:58,715
Tell me about yourself.

320
00:22:02,620 --> 00:22:04,954
My father found me strange.

321
00:22:06,957 --> 00:22:08,891
Sent me to Bedlam as a child.

322
00:22:08,893 --> 00:22:10,359
Bedlam?

323
00:22:10,361 --> 00:22:11,728
A madhouse?

324
00:22:12,930 --> 00:22:14,997
It was Thomas who found me there.

325
00:22:14,999 --> 00:22:16,966
Took me home.

326
00:22:16,968 --> 00:22:18,367
Thomas and his wife, Emily,

327
00:22:18,369 --> 00:22:22,071
they raised me as their own.

328
00:22:22,073 --> 00:22:24,140
She died two months back.

329
00:22:25,475 --> 00:22:27,008
So he married you.

330
00:22:29,145 --> 00:22:32,047
Thomas is educating me
by way of experiment.

331
00:22:32,049 --> 00:22:35,050
I'm interested in surgical procedure

332
00:22:35,052 --> 00:22:37,419
and the function of organs.

333
00:22:37,421 --> 00:22:38,587
You've cut into a living thing?

334
00:22:40,590 --> 00:22:43,524
I held a beating heart in my hand once,

335
00:22:43,526 --> 00:22:45,093
and I wrote a paper about it.

336
00:22:45,095 --> 00:22:46,694
It was published,

337
00:22:46,696 --> 00:22:48,130
under Thomas's name, of course.

338
00:22:48,132 --> 00:22:50,932
I am shown at scientific gatherings.

339
00:22:50,934 --> 00:22:52,667
I am called "The woman of genius."

340
00:22:52,669 --> 00:22:54,870
They tell me my abilities
derive from my head,

341
00:22:54,872 --> 00:22:55,871
which is too small,

342
00:22:55,873 --> 00:22:56,838
and my brain, which is over-large,

343
00:22:56,840 --> 00:22:58,140
and presses acutely against my skull,

344
00:22:58,142 --> 00:22:59,907
and these facts, I am told,

345
00:22:59,909 --> 00:23:02,076
explain my facilities
with numbers and processes.

346
00:23:12,053 --> 00:23:14,889
What if that man, Slotter, comes back?

347
00:23:15,924 --> 00:23:19,093
He has no claim.

348
00:23:19,095 --> 00:23:20,895
They're my daughters.

349
00:23:26,902 --> 00:23:28,735
You would kill him?

350
00:23:36,678 --> 00:23:39,179
Out here...

351
00:23:39,181 --> 00:23:41,047
That's all you need.

352
00:23:42,983 --> 00:23:45,619
Hey!

353
00:23:45,621 --> 00:23:47,754
[Giggling]

354
00:23:47,756 --> 00:23:49,555
[Distant shot blasts]

355
00:23:50,925 --> 00:23:54,194
They've found game.

356
00:23:54,196 --> 00:23:56,830
We'll feast tonight in celebration.

357
00:23:57,832 --> 00:24:00,599
[Another shot blasts]

358
00:24:15,582 --> 00:24:17,216
Why haven't they returned?

359
00:24:17,218 --> 00:24:18,517
I'm worried.

360
00:24:18,519 --> 00:24:20,720
There's another story I will tell you.

361
00:24:22,121 --> 00:24:23,188
Apaches,

362
00:24:23,190 --> 00:24:25,858
fiercest Indians of all.

363
00:24:25,860 --> 00:24:29,161
They tie men to stakes
and light 'em on fire.

364
00:24:29,163 --> 00:24:30,262
The big ones got enough fat on them

365
00:24:30,264 --> 00:24:31,496
they'll burn all night.

366
00:24:31,498 --> 00:24:34,867
[Cackles, wheezing]

367
00:24:34,869 --> 00:24:37,869
Of course, the Indians hereabouts,

368
00:24:37,871 --> 00:24:39,538
they got their own tricks.

369
00:24:40,806 --> 00:24:42,006
Ask her.

370
00:24:42,008 --> 00:24:44,075
She knows.

371
00:24:44,077 --> 00:24:47,612
Now, I hear she buried
a child the other day.

372
00:24:47,614 --> 00:24:49,347
Buries one,

373
00:24:49,349 --> 00:24:51,916
two spring up,

374
00:24:51,918 --> 00:24:52,950
two more.

375
00:24:54,586 --> 00:24:56,420
She's got the dark power, that one.

376
00:24:57,422 --> 00:25:00,457
Why don't you ask her where
all your men have gone!

377
00:25:00,459 --> 00:25:01,492
You shut up!

378
00:25:01,494 --> 00:25:02,727
You're drunk.

379
00:25:02,729 --> 00:25:03,728
And a fool.

380
00:25:03,730 --> 00:25:05,029
I know you,

381
00:25:05,031 --> 00:25:06,664
from a poster I saw somewhere.

382
00:25:06,666 --> 00:25:08,365
[Bottle clanks]

383
00:25:08,367 --> 00:25:09,366
Hey!

384
00:25:09,368 --> 00:25:10,367
[Horse whinnies distantly]

385
00:25:10,369 --> 00:25:11,935
They're back. They're back!

386
00:25:11,937 --> 00:25:13,504
Neill! Neill!

387
00:25:13,506 --> 00:25:14,637
[Crowd murmuring]

388
00:25:14,639 --> 00:25:16,573
[Kat]: Georgie!

389
00:25:17,508 --> 00:25:18,508
[Cocks gun]

390
00:25:19,577 --> 00:25:21,111
- [Fires]
- [Gasps of shock]

391
00:25:21,113 --> 00:25:21,978
Indians!

392
00:25:21,980 --> 00:25:23,080
[Screams of terror]

393
00:25:23,082 --> 00:25:24,081
[Laughing]

394
00:25:25,717 --> 00:25:26,783
Run!

395
00:25:29,486 --> 00:25:32,388
[Women and horses screaming]

396
00:25:34,057 --> 00:25:35,091
[Screams]

397
00:25:38,462 --> 00:25:39,829
[Screaming in terror and panic]

398
00:26:00,155 --> 00:26:02,223
[Sobbing in anguish]

399
00:26:11,532 --> 00:26:14,668
[Distant cries of grief]

400
00:26:16,671 --> 00:26:18,705
Kelly!

401
00:26:18,707 --> 00:26:20,874
Boys!

402
00:26:28,416 --> 00:26:31,151
Jeremiah!

403
00:26:42,663 --> 00:26:45,131
[Weeping]

404
00:27:07,253 --> 00:27:10,522
[Dripping]

405
00:27:33,145 --> 00:27:34,245
I found him in the tall grass.

406
00:27:34,247 --> 00:27:35,847
A concussion, I think.

407
00:27:35,849 --> 00:27:37,248
He has yet to regain consciousness.

408
00:27:37,250 --> 00:27:39,350
It was Slotter who did this.

409
00:27:39,352 --> 00:27:41,518
It's Indians, we saw.

410
00:27:41,520 --> 00:27:43,754
[Hoofbeats approach]

411
00:27:48,560 --> 00:27:50,962
Mrs. Loving!

412
00:27:51,054 --> 00:27:52,953
Whoa...

413
00:27:52,955 --> 00:27:55,923
Saw smoke at first light.

414
00:27:55,925 --> 00:27:58,992
Not a one left standing.

415
00:27:58,994 --> 00:28:00,794
Goddamn Indians.

416
00:28:02,029 --> 00:28:03,897
Oh, you'd shoot an unarmed man?

417
00:28:03,899 --> 00:28:05,866
It'd be a womanly thing to do.

418
00:28:05,868 --> 00:28:07,501
Where are my girls?

419
00:28:07,503 --> 00:28:09,035
Where's my boy and my husband?

420
00:28:09,037 --> 00:28:10,036
Ask the savages.

421
00:28:10,038 --> 00:28:11,371
Where are they?

422
00:28:18,745 --> 00:28:20,113
[Screams]

423
00:28:20,115 --> 00:28:21,747
Shh, shh, shh...

424
00:28:21,749 --> 00:28:22,915
[Yells in protest]

425
00:28:25,118 --> 00:28:26,719
[Screams, choking]

426
00:28:33,026 --> 00:28:34,594
[Gasping for air]

427
00:28:34,596 --> 00:28:35,661
[Gun clatters away]

428
00:28:40,433 --> 00:28:41,766
Leave her be.

429
00:28:47,507 --> 00:28:50,976
You killed that boy!

430
00:28:50,978 --> 00:28:52,944
For taunting at you.

431
00:28:52,946 --> 00:28:55,881
Cut a child's tongue from his mouth!

432
00:28:55,883 --> 00:28:57,449
Woman's crazed!

433
00:28:58,450 --> 00:29:00,051
The Indians are still out there.

434
00:29:00,053 --> 00:29:03,520
We're taking you to a safe place.

435
00:29:04,555 --> 00:29:08,427
You're welcome as well, of course.

436
00:29:08,829 --> 00:29:11,095
There's always room for, uh,

437
00:29:11,097 --> 00:29:13,665
beauty.

438
00:29:17,002 --> 00:29:17,968
[Groaning softly]

439
00:29:19,438 --> 00:29:21,072
My gut...

440
00:29:21,074 --> 00:29:23,141
[Wincing]

441
00:29:23,208 --> 00:29:25,541
It's burning up inside.

442
00:29:28,979 --> 00:29:31,546
I'm fine.

443
00:29:37,988 --> 00:29:38,988
They're fools.

444
00:29:38,990 --> 00:29:41,624
They're in shock,

445
00:29:41,626 --> 00:29:42,992
and we have no choice but to go.

446
00:29:42,994 --> 00:29:44,259
I must go with them.

447
00:29:45,194 --> 00:29:46,762
They're cattle,

448
00:29:46,764 --> 00:29:49,931
too stupid to think for themselves,

449
00:29:49,933 --> 00:29:52,734
and so are you.

450
00:29:54,103 --> 00:29:56,904
We are just afraid.

451
00:29:56,906 --> 00:30:00,542
We are not like you.

452
00:30:17,026 --> 00:30:19,027
Be careful. Be careful.

453
00:30:34,142 --> 00:30:37,044
No women were killed.

454
00:30:37,046 --> 00:30:39,245
Not one.

455
00:30:39,247 --> 00:30:40,346
What do you think that means?

456
00:30:43,918 --> 00:30:45,218
Come with us.

457
00:30:45,220 --> 00:30:48,088
It is too dangerous on your own.

458
00:30:48,090 --> 00:30:50,023
Jeremiah will not know where to find me.

459
00:30:51,659 --> 00:30:52,358
And your girls?

460
00:30:54,061 --> 00:30:55,995
Slotter has them.

461
00:30:57,264 --> 00:30:58,931
Then we must get them back.

462
00:31:17,884 --> 00:31:19,284
[Women weep in grief]

463
00:31:40,408 --> 00:31:42,575
[Bustle of town outside]

464
00:31:48,348 --> 00:31:50,016
[Talking quietly]

465
00:31:50,018 --> 00:31:52,018
<i>Stay back here, girls.</i>

466
00:31:55,689 --> 00:31:58,490
[Rain pattering]

467
00:32:12,472 --> 00:32:13,939
Is this Montana?

468
00:32:13,941 --> 00:32:15,674
No.

469
00:32:15,676 --> 00:32:17,142
Too far north.

470
00:32:17,144 --> 00:32:18,477
Where are we, then?

471
00:32:21,815 --> 00:32:24,516
You're icing on a teacake, old bird.

472
00:32:24,518 --> 00:32:27,118
Warm end to a cold night on the range.

473
00:32:30,022 --> 00:32:32,023
Welcome, ladies.

474
00:32:32,025 --> 00:32:33,491
Be seein' you.

475
00:32:34,526 --> 00:32:36,494
You're in Janestown now.

476
00:32:36,496 --> 00:32:39,564
You're Jane, and Jane,

477
00:32:39,566 --> 00:32:42,567
and Jane.

478
00:32:42,569 --> 00:32:45,603
There's not a body here
worries you got your own name,

479
00:32:45,605 --> 00:32:48,072
or a soul who wants saving.

480
00:32:49,274 --> 00:32:51,342
Your men...

481
00:32:51,344 --> 00:32:53,511
will be lying in graves next to whores.

482
00:32:55,113 --> 00:32:56,514
Took by cholera.

483
00:32:56,516 --> 00:32:59,350
12 girls dead.

484
00:32:59,352 --> 00:33:00,985
You to take their place.

485
00:33:02,553 --> 00:33:07,557
You're wanting husbands,
and lovers, and sweethearts,

486
00:33:07,559 --> 00:33:10,361
you'll end up lying with the likes of him,

487
00:33:10,363 --> 00:33:11,395
or worse.

488
00:33:13,231 --> 00:33:15,032
Find your way outta here.

489
00:33:15,034 --> 00:33:18,502
To kin and home.

490
00:33:18,504 --> 00:33:21,404
The two girls Slotter was
asking after at Station House,

491
00:33:21,406 --> 00:33:24,774
are they here?

492
00:33:26,176 --> 00:33:29,445
Over there.

493
00:33:54,571 --> 00:33:57,339
[Pebbles clatter]

494
00:33:57,341 --> 00:33:58,340
Isabelle...

495
00:33:58,342 --> 00:33:59,307
Isabelle!

496
00:34:01,277 --> 00:34:02,745
Now, that's enough,

497
00:34:02,747 --> 00:34:05,213
this grieving and carrying on.

498
00:34:06,516 --> 00:34:07,783
No...

499
00:34:09,052 --> 00:34:10,052
there will be no...

500
00:34:10,054 --> 00:34:11,420
no damn...

501
00:34:11,422 --> 00:34:13,422
there will be no stone.

502
00:34:13,424 --> 00:34:16,358
A grave in the yard of a pleasure house

503
00:34:16,360 --> 00:34:19,561
is not conducive to the
entertaining of investors.

504
00:34:19,563 --> 00:34:22,097
You go to hell!

505
00:34:22,099 --> 00:34:24,232
Pull yourself together.

506
00:34:26,602 --> 00:34:28,636
Jared!

507
00:34:28,638 --> 00:34:30,471
Fill up the...

508
00:34:30,473 --> 00:34:33,140
damn hole.

509
00:34:38,814 --> 00:34:41,482
Who are the women in the cribs?

510
00:34:41,484 --> 00:34:43,650
They're widows.

511
00:34:43,652 --> 00:34:45,786
Husbands were murdered by Indians.

512
00:34:45,788 --> 00:34:47,621
We'll give them work.

513
00:34:47,623 --> 00:34:50,357
You let them finish their grieving.

514
00:34:54,096 --> 00:34:57,631
Those girls I brought shall
be ready to work tonight.

515
00:34:57,633 --> 00:34:59,299
They're too young to whore!

516
00:34:59,301 --> 00:35:00,601
They work!

517
00:35:00,603 --> 00:35:01,602
Tonight!

518
00:35:11,112 --> 00:35:12,412
Robin and Kelly are at that house.

519
00:35:12,414 --> 00:35:14,380
There's a gathering there tonight.

520
00:35:14,382 --> 00:35:16,382
He intends them whores.

521
00:35:16,384 --> 00:35:17,517
We can't leave them.

522
00:35:19,453 --> 00:35:22,622
What are you going to do?

523
00:35:23,824 --> 00:35:24,824
It's for our ranch.

524
00:35:26,193 --> 00:35:27,594
For stock.

525
00:35:28,596 --> 00:35:30,330
I'm going to get them back.

526
00:35:36,075 --> 00:35:39,110
<i>Gentlemen. Now, ranchers among you know,</i>

527
00:35:39,112 --> 00:35:40,245
that this place here

528
00:35:40,247 --> 00:35:44,015
offers some of the finest
pastures in the world.

529
00:35:44,017 --> 00:35:45,784
Our freight cars will
hold not only your cattle,

530
00:35:45,786 --> 00:35:47,886
but coal,

531
00:35:47,888 --> 00:35:50,221
from what promises to
be the largest coal mine

532
00:35:50,223 --> 00:35:51,790
on the continent.

533
00:35:51,792 --> 00:35:54,124
This is your opportunity
to invest in that coal mine.

534
00:35:54,126 --> 00:35:57,595
You'll be the first in, and richer for it.

535
00:35:59,030 --> 00:36:01,365
Now enjoy the evening!

536
00:36:01,367 --> 00:36:03,000
Gentlemen,

537
00:36:03,002 --> 00:36:05,169
for your pleasure...

538
00:36:05,171 --> 00:36:07,305
[Applauding and cheering]

539
00:36:07,307 --> 00:36:08,839
[Clapping] Oh, yeah.

540
00:36:23,354 --> 00:36:24,855
[Quietly] Come with me.

541
00:36:24,857 --> 00:36:27,857
You, sir, can piss up a tree...

542
00:36:27,859 --> 00:36:29,158
It's her.

543
00:36:31,061 --> 00:36:32,395
You've come for us.

544
00:36:35,232 --> 00:36:37,033
[Slotter making deals]

545
00:36:43,941 --> 00:36:45,842
Sir?

546
00:36:45,844 --> 00:36:47,009
What is this?

547
00:36:47,011 --> 00:36:48,744
The gentleman would
like us both for an hour.

548
00:36:48,746 --> 00:36:50,679
Okay, well, get up there, then.

549
00:36:50,681 --> 00:36:52,281
Upstairs.

550
00:37:07,230 --> 00:37:08,764
The doctor's coming.

551
00:37:26,182 --> 00:37:27,448
You're okay?

552
00:37:27,450 --> 00:37:29,317
No one messed with us.

553
00:37:29,319 --> 00:37:32,987
We wait. Stay a bit. We'll be out.

554
00:37:35,824 --> 00:37:38,693
[Knock on door]

555
00:37:40,061 --> 00:37:41,996
You're the doctor?

556
00:37:43,932 --> 00:37:46,300
Came as soon as sent for.

557
00:37:48,737 --> 00:37:49,736
I bloody told you

558
00:37:49,738 --> 00:37:51,772
that those girls are too young to whore!

559
00:37:51,774 --> 00:37:52,839
Isabelle...

560
00:37:52,841 --> 00:37:56,777
This is the doctor.

561
00:37:56,779 --> 00:37:58,279
Well,

562
00:37:58,281 --> 00:38:00,247
I have no faith in a woman doctoring.

563
00:38:00,249 --> 00:38:02,983
I have some training, Mrs. Slotter.

564
00:38:06,153 --> 00:38:08,054
What is your trouble?

565
00:38:08,056 --> 00:38:09,055
Bellyache.

566
00:38:09,057 --> 00:38:10,891
It's his conscience pricking.

567
00:38:12,993 --> 00:38:14,461
Most times, fit to puke.

568
00:38:14,463 --> 00:38:17,997
'Twas meat I ate two days past.

569
00:38:17,999 --> 00:38:19,900
The day your child was born?

570
00:38:22,002 --> 00:38:24,938
What is this?

571
00:38:24,940 --> 00:38:28,074
This is Isabelle's tonic.

572
00:38:28,076 --> 00:38:29,875
I just started. It helps some.

573
00:38:29,877 --> 00:38:31,777
[Sniffing]

574
00:38:32,947 --> 00:38:35,148
I can offer you the recipe.

575
00:38:35,150 --> 00:38:36,849
You must keep it to yourself.

576
00:38:38,452 --> 00:38:39,919
I shall get back to our guests.

577
00:38:41,154 --> 00:38:43,889
You take your rest.

578
00:39:01,507 --> 00:39:04,242
Miss Kelly!

579
00:39:04,244 --> 00:39:05,844
Ma'am...

580
00:39:05,846 --> 00:39:07,212
The gentleman was needing a drink,

581
00:39:07,214 --> 00:39:08,847
so I just brought him...

582
00:39:10,483 --> 00:39:12,116
Let them go.

583
00:39:12,118 --> 00:39:14,285
The house owns these girls.

584
00:39:14,287 --> 00:39:15,987
You know what it is to lose a child.

585
00:39:15,989 --> 00:39:18,322
Let them go.

586
00:39:18,324 --> 00:39:19,423
[Slotter]: Izzy!

587
00:39:21,026 --> 00:39:22,861
Isabelle!

588
00:39:24,930 --> 00:39:26,831
The women who arrived
in the cribs last night,

589
00:39:26,833 --> 00:39:29,033
it was your husband killed their men.

590
00:39:29,035 --> 00:39:30,401
It was Indians.

591
00:39:30,403 --> 00:39:31,869
He killed my boy.

592
00:39:31,871 --> 00:39:34,071
Strung him up in a
tree. Cut his tongue out.

593
00:39:34,073 --> 00:39:35,206
It was Indians,

594
00:39:35,208 --> 00:39:36,240
and you're a liar.

595
00:39:36,242 --> 00:39:37,875
[Slotter]: Isabelle?

596
00:39:37,877 --> 00:39:39,310
Don't call to him.

597
00:39:39,312 --> 00:39:41,178
You keep quiet,

598
00:39:41,180 --> 00:39:42,946
or I will tell him about your tonic.

599
00:39:44,449 --> 00:39:47,951
Arsenic will kill a man, not heal him.

600
00:39:47,953 --> 00:39:52,589
You were deliberate in your intention.

601
00:39:57,595 --> 00:40:00,263
My husband took my child's
body and put it out.

602
00:40:01,832 --> 00:40:03,199
There was a coyote there.

603
00:40:04,902 --> 00:40:06,569
She was bitten.

604
00:40:06,571 --> 00:40:07,870
She was tasted.

605
00:40:10,274 --> 00:40:12,575
Get out.

606
00:40:19,482 --> 00:40:21,884
[Slotter]: Isabelle!

607
00:40:21,886 --> 00:40:22,885
I'm coming!

608
00:40:30,160 --> 00:40:32,494
God forgive me.

609
00:40:32,496 --> 00:40:34,629
Izzy?

610
00:40:51,180 --> 00:40:53,648
Are you feeling any better?

611
00:40:53,650 --> 00:40:55,316
Whiskey's the healer.

612
00:40:57,152 --> 00:40:58,987
[Chuckles mirthlessly]

613
00:41:17,672 --> 00:41:20,641
Sleep of angels.

614
00:41:42,463 --> 00:41:43,497
Thank you, ma'am.

615
00:41:43,499 --> 00:41:45,265
For everything.

616
00:41:48,569 --> 00:41:49,569
I found this.

617
00:41:49,571 --> 00:41:50,637
It's yours.

618
00:41:54,408 --> 00:41:57,476
You saw me take it.

619
00:41:57,478 --> 00:41:58,678
I'm awful sorry for the trick.

620
00:41:58,680 --> 00:42:00,079
I won't ever again.

621
00:42:00,081 --> 00:42:03,315
Thomas gave it to me.

622
00:42:03,317 --> 00:42:04,550
A wedding gift.

623
00:42:05,585 --> 00:42:08,087
Well, hearts mean love.

624
00:42:09,389 --> 00:42:12,324
A heart is a pump.

625
00:42:17,330 --> 00:42:19,298
Good night.

626
00:42:19,300 --> 00:42:20,332
Good night.

627
00:42:20,334 --> 00:42:23,335
[Crashing outside]

628
00:42:25,004 --> 00:42:26,372
[Bottles clanking]

629
00:42:27,641 --> 00:42:29,441
Is it him?

630
00:42:29,443 --> 00:42:31,509
Bear, could be.

631
00:42:31,511 --> 00:42:33,211
Or coyote.

632
00:42:33,213 --> 00:42:34,279
He won't be back here tonight.

633
00:42:35,715 --> 00:42:37,315
We're safe to sleep?

634
00:42:37,317 --> 00:42:38,650
Yes.

635
00:42:51,263 --> 00:42:53,431
You know this is Canada, ma.

636
00:42:53,433 --> 00:42:55,657
There is no law here but our own.

637
00:43:23,333 --> 00:43:24,794
<i>My husband is not a murderer.</i>

638
00:43:24,796 --> 00:43:26,729
<i>He killed 20 men.</i>

639
00:43:26,731 --> 00:43:28,163
You shut your mouth!

640
00:43:28,165 --> 00:43:30,165
<i>I'll ride out, find Jeremiah and Neil.</i>

641
00:43:30,167 --> 00:43:31,367
What if they're dead?

642
00:43:31,369 --> 00:43:33,135
No! Mama!

643
00:43:33,137 --> 00:43:34,337
<i>Take me instead.</i>

644
